# Data Model Notes

## Source
Raw relational data extracted from **DBeaver**.

## Normalization Steps (Power Query Editor)

### Patient Table
- Removed duplicate patient records
- Standardized name formatting (First + Last)
- Resolved missing gender values → tagged as `Unspecified`
- Created Age Group buckets: `39-`, `40-64`, `65+`

### Case Table
- Normalized case type labels (e.g. trimmed whitespace, standardized casing)
- Mapped case statuses to standard categories
- Linked cases to patients via Patient ID foreign key

### Insurance Table
- Identified records with missing Insurance Name or Insurance ID
- Flagged as `[Missing]` for separate analysis
- Linked to cases via Case ID

### Doctor Table
- Deduplicated doctor records
- Aggregated Billed, Paid, Dedcop, Adjustment, Balance per doctor

### Attorney Table
- Normalized firm names
- Linked attorney fees to case records by year

### User Table
- Identified active vs inactive users based on billing activity
- Aggregated performance metrics: Billed, Paid, Adjustment, Dedcop, Balance

